STUNNED cops say they discovered a haul of drugs and weapons when they pulled over a motorist for driving the wrong direction down a one way street.Officers stopped the car in the Saltmarket area on Tuesday night when they spotted it being driven the wrong way.After becoming aware of a &quot;suspicious smell,&quot; police searched the vehicle and discovered drugs, believed to be cannabis, a knife and wooden bat.A 25-year-old man was arrested in connection with road traffic, offensive weapons and drugs offences.Inspector Gavin Smith said: &quot;Officers stopped the car and drugs were recovered.&quot;A knife and wooden bat were also found within the vehicle.&quot;A 25-year-old man was arrested.&quot;Police said the vehicle was originally stopped as part of Scottish Road Safety week.A report is expected to be sent to prosecutors.